snippet: Few voters expect President Obama to seriously change Washington; most just want him to make it function.
abstract: News analysis; Pres Obama's next battle is to decide what he wants to accomplish in second term and how to go about it; he will have to choose between conciliation and confrontation with a Congress still at least partly controlled by Republicans, or find a way to toggle back and forth between the two.
lead_paragraph: Few voters expect President Obama to seriously change Washington; most just want him to make it function.
